(1296, 'nirvana', '\\x3e\\x64\\x7f\\x66\\x8f\\x8d\\x62\\x55', , '2005-08-23 02:25:05', '2005-08-23 05:23:54', 1, 1, 'itjobs@nirvanabpo.com', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '2011-04-26 10:56:23', 0, 'Kripamaye Samantaray', '080', '51103300', '271', '080', '28525100', '271', '080', '51103301', '271', '080', '28525900', '', 'Nirvana is a business process outsourcing solutions provider founded two years ago by Raj Kondur. Raj was previously the Co-Founder of ChrysCapital, India''s largest Venture Capital fund with $ 450 mn under management. He spearheaded the firm''s investments in the BPO space and was a founding member of Spectramind (now Wipro Spectramind). His prior experience includes several years with Morgan Stanley and AT Kearney in the US. Raj is an alumnus of Harvard Business School.\r\n\r\nNirvana is led by a world-class management team that been responsible for shaping and delivering true value added outsourcing initiatives for several renowned organizations including AT Kearney, GE, Morgan Stanley, Reuters, KPMG, Microland, and other leading enterprises. We have also been involved in setting up and managing some of India''s largest process solution providers. Nirvana?s board of advisors and investors include senior executives from McKinsey (Rajat Gupta), Citigroup (Victor Menezes), Morgan Stanley (Richard Fisher, Standard Chartered (Rana Talwar), Lehman Brothers (Jawahar Chirimar) and others.\r\n\r\nNirvana spent over 18 months building a world-class organization before going out to the market ? ironing out the typical Offshoring issues, assembling one of the best teams in the business, and adding scope, scale and operating depth. Since then Nirvana has gained considerable traction in the marketplace, received customer kudos, and also won away demanding customers from other big BPO companies due to its unique depth and ability to deliver significantly higher value. It has been regarded by Kleiner Perkins Caufield and Byers as the most interesting BPO opportunity in the market, and its technology environment has been rated by Cisco Systems as the best in the world. Visit www.nirvanabpo.com', 'Nirvana is a business process outsourcing solutions provider founded two years ago by Raj Kondur. Raj was previously the Co-Founder of ChrysCapital, India''s largest Venture Capital fund with $ 450 mn under management. He spearheaded the firm''s investments in the BPO space and was a founding member of Spectramind (now Wipro Spectramind). His prior experience includes several years with Morgan Stanley and AT Kearney in the US. Raj is an alumnus of Harvard Business School.\r\n\r\nNirvana is led by a world-class management team that been responsible for shaping and delivering true value added outsourcing initiatives for several renowned organizations including AT Kearney, GE, Morgan Stanley, Reuters, KPMG, Microland, and other leading enterprises. We have also been involved in setting up and managing some of India''s largest process solution providers. Nirvana?s board of advisors and investors include senior executives from McKinsey (Rajat Gupta), Citigroup (Victor Menezes), Morgan Stanley (Richard Fisher, Standard Chartered (Rana Talwar), Lehman Brothers (Jawahar Chirimar) and others.\r\n\r\nNirvana spent over 18 months building a world-class organization before going out to the market ? ironing out the typical Offshoring issues, assembling one of the best teams in the business, and adding scope, scale and operating depth. Since then Nirvana has gained considerable traction in the marketplace, received customer kudos, and also won away demanding customers from other big BPO companies due to its unique depth and ability to deliver significantly higher value. It has been regarded by Kleiner Perkins Caufield and Byers as the most interesting BPO opportunity in the market, and its technology environment has been rated by Cisco Systems as the best in the world. Visit www.nirvanabpo.com', 32, 'HR Executive', '', 0, 'Nirvana Business Solution