(1498, 'siptech', '\\x4c\\xcb\\x74\\x69\\xc5\\x93\\x6d\\x41\\x53\\x54\\xcc\\xde\\x8a\\xba\\xf0\\x78', , '2005-08-29 23:46:33', '2005-08-29 23:46:33', 1, 1, 'jasmine@siptech.com', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 'Jasmine Charlet', '044', '22541473', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '044', '22541475', '', 'SIPTECH''s key software processes were successfully assessed at the Maturity Level 4 of the SEI''s CMMi. We are proud to join a select group of software companies worldwide, which have achieved this level of capability maturity in its processes. \r\n\r\nSIPTECH, an ISO 9001:2000, is a leading provider of solutions and services in the areas of turnkey testing, technology solutions, application development and infrastructure management. The company''s value proposition is to provide these solutions and services that leverages on the low costs offered by offshore markets and the high quality of the offering gained through extensive experience, expertise and effective use of tools. This expertise and experience has been built over the last 6 years through projects delivered by a competent pool of engineers and through the partnerships with leading technology innovators like Sun Microsystems and Zaplet. \r\n\r\nSIP Technologies and Exports ("SIPTECH") has been a pioneer in outsourced testing, platform porting and outsourced product development services in the technology and telecommunication verticals. We are development partners with Sun Microsystems on the Java Soft Products. We are the Global Testing Center for Motorola''s next generation of mobile phones called JUIX or the Java User Interface experience. Motorola and its development teams in Mountain view, California, Sao Palo, Brazil, and Beijing, China depend on SIPTECH''s people, processes, and intellectual property to ensure a high quality, trouble free, and feature rich mobile communication experience for its customers. \r\n\r\nSIPTECH has made key contributions (1300 man-months) to the development of today''s de facto programming language, Java, and the J2EE framework through its work on the Java Compatibility Kit (JCK), the Technology Compatibility Kit (TCK), and the Compatibility Test Suite (CTS).\r\n\r\nSIPTECH today has about 90 employees in India and the US. It has had a consistent track record of growth and profitability from its inception barring an outlier period in 2002-2003.\r\n\r\nSIPTECH has decided to make further substantial investments in becoming a leader in IT Services and exploiting the still growing demand for offshore based IT services and business process outsourcing. The company''s growth will be based on its unique business model called Intellectual Property Enables Services (IPES) that combines a solution based and customized services approach to solving specific business problems in specific industry verticals. SIPTECH believes that IPES together with an industry and business solution focus will provide a compelling value proposition to its customers.', 'SIPTECH''s key software processes were successfully assessed at the Maturity Level 4 of the SEI''s CMMi. We are proud to join a select group of software companies worldwide, which have achieved this level of capability maturity in its processes. \r\n\r\nSIPTECH, an ISO 9001:2000, is a leading provider of solutions and services in the areas of turnkey testing, technology solutions, application development and infrastructure management. The company''s value proposition is to provide these solutions and services that leverages on the low costs offered by offshore markets and the high quality of the offering gained through extensive experience, expertise and effective use of tools. This expertise and experience has been built over the last 6 years through projects delivered by a competent pool of engineers and through the partnerships with leading technology innovators like Sun Microsystems and Zaplet. \r\n\r\nSIP Technologies and Exports ("SIPTECH") has been a pioneer in outsourced testing, platform porting and outsourced product development services in the technology and telecommunication verticals. We are development partners with Sun Microsystems on the Java Soft Products. We are the Global Testing Center for Motorola''s next generation of mobile phones called JUIX or the Java User Interface experience. Motorola and its development teams in Mountain view, California, Sao Palo, Brazil, and Beijing, China depend on SIPTECH''s people, processes, and intellectual property to ensure a high quality, trouble free, and feature rich mobile communication experience for its customers. \r\n\r\nSIPTECH has made key contributions (1300 man-months) to the development of today''s de facto programming language, Java, and the J2EE framework through its work on the Java Compatibility Kit (JCK), the Technology Compatibility Kit (TCK), and the Compatibility Test Suite (CTS).\r\n\r\nSIPTECH today has about 90 employees in India and the US. It has had a consistent track record of growth and profitability from its inception barring an outlier period in 2002-2003.\r\n\r\nSIPTECH has decided to make further substantial investments in becoming a leader in IT Services and exploiting the still growing demand for offshore based IT services and business process outsourcing. The company''s growth will be based on its unique business model called Intellectual Property Enables Services (IPES) that combines a solution based and customized services approach to solving specific business problems in specific industry verticals. SIPTECH believes that IPES together with an industry and business solution focus will provide a compelling value proposition to its customers.', 1, 'Human Resource Executive', 'jasmine@siptech.com', 0, 'SIPTECH', 'G4, Elnet Software City, CPT Road, Taramani, Chennai - 600 113.', 'IN', 'TN', 540, '', 2, 28, 6, 7, 5, 3, 22, 'www.siptech.com', '', '', ''),
